    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>By some misfortune, my <del>
                        <gap unit="chars" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/>
                    </del> Baggage does not reach me till <sic>too morrow</sic>. the sheets of
                    the <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bidb.xml#bi0013">welsh tour</title>
                    </bibl>
                    are in it. but you may depend on having them done to <choice>
                        <abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>your</expan>
                    </choice> mind &amp; sent by <persName ref="pe0065">my Son</persName>
                    the week following the next. They shall be left for you at <persName ref="pe0328">Faulders</persName>. The <hi rend="underline">let
                        in</hi> copies shall be properly attended to. I can give you a <del>great
                        copy</del>
                    <add place="above">
                        <persName ref="pe0321">Sir J. Wynne</persName>
                    </add>
                    but there are none on great paper So you must let it in.</p>
                <p>There are to be sold at <persName ref="pe0026">White</persName>'s three
                    very fine drawings of <persName ref="pe0014">Moses Griffiths</persName>
                    &amp; one of <persName ref="pe0330">P. Sandby</persName>'s. they are
                            <del>
                        <gap unit="chars" quantity="3" reason="illegible"/>
                    </del> the
                    property <del>of</del> to poor <persName ref="pe0014">moses</persName>,
                    so if you hear <sic>any body</sic> wish to have some of his works, I beg to
                    recommend. &amp; also puff off his <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0027">X
                        plates</rs> of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bidb.xml#bi0013">
                            <choice>
                                <abbr>suppl.</abbr>
                                <expan>supplement</expan>
                            </choice> to Snowdon</title>
                    </bibl>.<note type="editorial">For the ten
                        supplemental plates to A Journey to Snowdon, see NLW 12710C, where they are
                        bound at the end of the volume; and NLW 12711C, which also includes nine out
                        of the ten bound at the end. LINK TO WORKS LIST: A Journey to Snowdon
                        (London: Henry Hughes: 1781)</note>
                </p>
                <p>My best <choice>
                        <abbr>Complim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi>
                        </abbr>
                        <expan>Compliments</expan>
                    </choice> attend <persName ref="pe0331">Miss Bull</persName>
                   <note type="editorial">Uncharacteristically, Pennant names Miss Bull, i.e.
                        Elizabeth Bull, alone here.</note>: no<del>t</del>r let <persName ref="pe0332">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Storer</persName> be
                    forgotten.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>adieu <lb/>
                        <choice>
                        <abbr>Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                            </abbr>
                        <expan>Yours</expan>
                    </choice> most truely</salute> <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">
                            <choice>
                                <abbr>Th.</abbr>
                                <expan>Thomas</expan>
                            </choice> Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0001">Downing</placeName> June 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. 1781.</dateline>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Excuse the inclosed.<note type="editorial">No enclosure has been
                            preserved.</note> If you want a <rs type="art" ref="ardb.xml#ar0028">
                            <persName ref="pe0333">
                                <choice>
                                    <abbr>rev<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                                    </abbr>
                                    <expan>reverend</expan>
                                </choice> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lloyd</persName>
                        </rs>
                       <note type="editorial">A line engraving by Peter Mazell of a watercolour by
                            Moses Griffith of John Lloyd, Caerwys, was published by Mazell in 1780
                            and is included in Pennant's extra-illustrated Tour in Wales TWO, NLW,
                            as well as in Pennant and Bull's copies of Literary life (NLW 12706E,
                            NLW 5502E).</note> you must buy him of <persName ref="pe0143">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Mazel</persName>
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0797">No 62 Portland street</placeName>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
